{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"c6f8023046c23760","type":"group","x":-1040,"y":340,"width":1306,"height":1340,"label":"Untitled group"},
		{"id":"22d06932f4c780b9","type":"group","x":1280,"y":0,"width":1275,"height":1256,"label":"Large Hero Cards"},
		{"id":"cc9112936140cf28","type":"group","x":3560,"y":-4,"width":940,"height":1260,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"8bb8b49108cbd003","type":"group","x":1220,"y":-500,"width":2560,"height":440,"label":"Untitled group"},
		{"id":"83ba3323f79800c6","type":"group","x":4580,"y":-60,"width":850,"height":440},
		{"id":"6e295f5964f72650","type":"group","x":860,"y":1400,"width":800,"height":440},
		{"id":"f24be5afc775fc0a","type":"group","x":-380,"y":-140,"width":624,"height":413},
		{
			"id":"7394cb76d5b179ec",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Search Is Present But De-Emphasized\n\nVery interesting.\n\nSearch exists.\n\nYet it's tiny.\n\nSometimes just an icon.\n\nSometimes hidden behind a bar.\n\nWhy?\n\nBecause discovery products know:\n\n```\nSearch =Known IntentExplore =Unknown Intent\n```\n\nMost users don't know what they want.\n\nThe screen is designed for:\n\n> Help me find something worth wanting.\n\nNot:\n\n> Retrieve something specific.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":280,
			"y":560,
			"width":380,
			"height":680
		},
		{
			"id":"2144a055364fcda6",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# **\"Get someone from idle browsing → first meaningful action.\"**\nA normal person sees:\n\n> Explore content.\n\nA designer sees:\n\n> Reduce decision-making cost until a user commits.\n\nThe real job isn't discovery.\n\nThe real job is:\n\n**\"Get someone from idle browsing → first meaningful action.\"**\n\nEvery screen here is engineered around that transition.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":280,
			"y":1390,
			"width":550,
			"height":460
		},
		{"id":"d268c516012b35c4","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123924.png","x":79,"y":360,"width":176,"height":399},
		{"id":"a6d443bd02e78473","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123835.png","x":-152,"y":360,"width":176,"height":399},
		{
			"id":"2b14fec4f81bc9af",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Every Card Answers \"Why Should I Care?\" Immediately\n\nLook at the card structures.\n\nGPT Store:\n\n```\nLogo\nName\nOne-line value proposition\n```\n\nHeadspace:\n\n```\nCategory\nOutcome\n```\n\nApp Store:\n\n```\nApp\nVisual preview\nUse case\n```\n\nNone require investigation.\n\nWithin 2 seconds users can decide:\n\n```\nRelevant\nNot relevant\n```\n\nThe hidden principle:\n\n**Discovery dies when evaluation becomes expensive.**\n\nThe best explore screens compress value into a glance.\n\nThat's particularly relevant for SideQuestHQ.\n\nInstead of:\n\n```\nMachine Learning Cohort\n42 lessons\n```\n\nThink:\n\n```\nBuild your first AI agent\nUnderstand how LLMs actually work\nGo from AI consumer to AI builder\n```\n\nThe card should communicate the transformation before the structure.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-620,
			"y":-1390,
			"width":430,
			"height":1260
		},
		{
			"id":"f13046e278a9f8eb",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Curated > Comprehensive\n\nNotice how little content is shown.\n\nThe GPT Store especially.\n\nInstead of:\n\n```\n10,000 GPTs\n```\n\nYou see:\n\n```\nFeaturedTrendingEditor's Picks\n```\n\nThis is a trust architecture.\n\nThe product is essentially saying:\n\n> Let us narrow the universe for you.\n\nGood exploration screens reduce effort.\n\nBad exploration screens expose inventory.\n\nThe user doesn't want more options.\n\nThey want fewer good options.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-10,
			"y":-869,
			"width":330,
			"height":649
		},
		{"id":"555f4841dcb978d8","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123805.png","x":65,"y":-120,"width":164,"height":372},
		{"id":"0cbec11e4237648f","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123757.png","x":-140,"y":-120,"width":165,"height":373},
		{"id":"6ea94bb9f67592e6","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123915.png","x":-355,"y":-120,"width":165,"height":373},
		{
			"id":"80252a2576c937ea",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### The Feed Creates \"Safe Exploration\"\n\nNotice how exploration happens.\n\nYou never fully commit.\n\nYou peek.\n\nYou browse.\n\nYou swipe.\n\nYou preview.\n\nEvery interaction is reversible.\n\nThis is crucial.\n\nBecause travel has massive commitment costs.\n\nThe UI compensates by making discovery feel risk-free.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":740,
			"y":-549,
			"width":380,
			"height":540
		},
		{
			"id":"dfa88f5b25b6957d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## What SideQuestHQ Should Steal From This\n\nNot the travel cards.\n\nThe aspiration mechanics.\n\nBecause learning is actually closer to travel than most people realize.\n\nA beginner learning screen says:\n\n```\nMachine Learning45 lessons32 hours\n```\n\nA travel-style learning screen says:\n\n```\nBuild your first AI agentSee how ChatGPT actually worksUnderstand the psychology behind habitsLearn enough Japanese to survive Tokyo\n```\n\nThe first sells content.\n\nThe second sells transformation.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":660,
			"y":-1139,
			"width":570,
			"height":540
		},
		{
			"id":"44631b26cf6a8311",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### The Scroll Pattern Mimics Daydreaming\n\nThis is deeper than it looks.\n\nNotice:\n\nBig image.\n\nBig image.\n\nBig image.\n\nBig image.\n\nThe UX is essentially:\n\n```\nVisual fantasy↓Visual fantasy↓Visual fantasy↓Visual fantasy\n```\n\nThe app intentionally creates mental simulation.\n\nThe user starts imagining:\n\n- being there\n- doing that\n- experiencing it\n\nThe brain partially rehearses the trip before purchase.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":340,
			"y":-654,
			"width":320,
			"height":750
		},
		{"id":"68635f1cb7496a87","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260623011235.png","x":-233,"y":788,"width":400,"height":225},
		{"id":"d10dde55c78c78c1","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260623011303.png","x":-355,"y":1108,"width":581,"height":385},
		{"id":"646d68f717c7d7f6","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123832.png","x":-372,"y":360,"width":177,"height":400},
		{
			"id":"d236a6e2421843ba",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==Masonry optimizes IDEAS/SEC OPTIMIZED==\n**Core Discovery UX Insight**\n\n- These products optimize for **\"I don't know what I'm looking for\"**, not search.\n- The **grid itself is the product**. Users visually filter interesting vs boring far faster than they can read titles.\n- Discovery happens through **peripheral vision**—users evaluate the current card, surrounding cards, and overall patterns simultaneously.\n- Layouts are engineered to create **accidental curiosity** (\"Wait, what's that?\").\n- They optimize for **serendipity over efficiency**:\n    - Search → shortest path to a known goal.\n    - Discovery → best unexpected find.\n- They feel more like **bookstores, galleries, and flea markets** than databases.\n\n###  **SideQuestHQ Application** - The key shift is from **topic browsing** to **rabbit-hole entry points**.\n\nInstead of:\n```text\nCategory → Course → Lessons\n```\nUse:\n```text\nCuriosity Trigger → Topic → Cohort → Learning Path\n```\nExamples:\n```text\n\"Why casinos remove clocks\"\n\"The AI that beat a human champion\"\n\"How Tokyo trains stay on time\"\n```\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-1000,
			"y":350,
			"width":520,
			"height":970
		},
		{
			"id":"c95045eb3350237f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"\n## **Biggest takeaway:** Discovery platforms assume curiosity will self-organize if users are exposed to enough interesting things. Most learning apps focus on filtering; the strongest ones focus on exploration.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-1000,
			"y":1350,
			"width":480,
			"height":260
		},
		{"id":"3c0ea62b18c23bc7","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124248.png","x":2720,"y":-461,"width":500,"height":375},
		{"id":"82ff7c557679c305","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124104.png","x":3123,"y":-465,"width":643,"height":382},
		{
			"id":"353490e07dfc00ee",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Social Proof Is Delayed\n\nNotice ratings and avatars are tiny.\n\nThis is fascinating.\n\nThe designers know:\n\nEarly-stage discovery is emotional.\n\nLate-stage commitment is rational.\n\nTherefore:\nStage \n1. EmotionStage \n2. ValidationStage \n3. Purchase\n\n==If ratings dominated immediately, they'd interrupt imagination.==",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3386,
			"y":-1040,
			"width":380,
			"height":480
		},
		{
			"id":"d1c1efeb59503770",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## The Giant Product Image Is Reducing Uncertainty\n\nClothing has an unusually high risk profile.\n\nUsers wonder:\n\n```\nWill it look good?Will it fit?Will I regret it?\n```\n\nThe oversized image exists to reduce uncertainty.\n\nThe image does more trust-building than paragraphs of copy.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2943,
			"y":-999,
			"width":360,
			"height":413
		},
		{
			"id":"7ca43cd925180ded",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## ==Size Selection Is A Friction Management System==\n\nThis is deeper than it looks.\n\nThe size selector isn't there for choice.\n\nIt's there for commitment.\n\nOnce someone selects:\n\n```\nXL\n```\n\nThey've mentally begun the purchase.\n\nBehavioral economists call this a micro-commitment.\n\nThe interaction changes the user from:\n\n```\nBrowser\n```\n\ninto:\n\n```\nPotential buyer\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3080,
			"y":688,
			"width":440,
			"height":651
		},
		{
			"id":"35d073879f6e079e",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3240,
			"y":380,
			"width":260,
			"height":60
		},
		{"id":"5a9620bdd21eaf19","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123641.png","x":5040,"y":-40,"width":177,"height":400},
		{
			"id":"5de36b99b51dd0db",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### ==Horizontal Rails Are Actually Context Switchers==\n\nMost people think these are categories.\n\nThey're not.\n\n```\nBasketball\nFootball\nF1\n```\n\naren't content.\n\nThey're mental modes.\n\nSwitching tabs changes:\n\n```\nidentitylanguageexpectations\n```\n\nThe user enters a different sports universe.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":5100,
			"y":460,
			"width":460,
			"height":580
		},
		{
			"id":"0b90ae536108b42f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Categories Are Emotional, Not Functional\n\nLook at examples:\n\n- Mountain\n- Beach\n- Camp\n\nThese aren't features.\n\nThey're moods.\n\nA better mental model is:\n\n```\nCategory=Desired emotional state\n```\n\nThe user isn't filtering locations.\n\nThey're filtering futures.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3123,
			"y":91,
			"width":380,
			"height":469
		},
		{
			"id":"8018c074bfea81c6",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## The Product Card Is Selling Scarcity\n\n#### Look at: ==**50% OFFFlash Sale**==\nVery intentional.\n\nFashion purchases are highly postponable.\n\nThe biggest enemy isn't rejection.\n\nIt's delay.\n\nThe UI constantly communicates:\n\n```\nBuy nownot later\n```\n\nBecause \"later\" often means never.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2660,
			"y":70,
			"width":420,
			"height":510
		},
		{
			"id":"7b5a16f5ddb14243",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## ==Orange Is Functioning As A Revenue Color==\n\nNotice where orange appears.\n\nNot everywhere.\n\nOnly around:\n\n- Shop Now\n- Buy Now\n- Add To Cart\n- Filters\n\nThis creates a visual hierarchy.\n\nYour eyes unconsciously learn:\n\n```\nOrange=Action\n```\n\nAfter a few minutes users stop reading buttons entirely.\n\nThey just hunt orange.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2622,
			"y":646,
			"width":382,
			"height":614
		},
		{
			"id":"b92b3ae395a25ffa",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# What SideQuestHQ Should Learn From This\n\nNot the ecommerce mechanics.\n\nThe transformation mechanics.\n\nNotice how fashion apps never lead with:\n\n```\n100% cotton320 GSMPolyester blend\n```\n\nThey lead with:\n\n```\nHow you'll feel.\n```\n\nMost learning apps make this mistake.\n\nThey present:\n\n```\n48 lessons32 hours12 modules\n```\n\nThat's equivalent to showing fabric composition.\n\nUsers care about outcomes.\n\nNot inventory.\n\nInstead of:\n\n```\nMachine Learning Cohort42 lessons\n```\n\nThink:\n\n```\nBuild AI projects confidentlyUnderstand how ChatGPT actually worksStop feeling lost when people discuss AIGo from curious to capable\n```\n\nThe fashion app sells a future version of the user.\n\nThe strongest learning products do exactly the same thing.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3766,
			"y":-1180,
			"width":660,
			"height":1060
		},
		{
			"id":"623185757cc695be",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### They Treat Sports as Ongoing Stories, Not Data\n\nA normal sports app would start with:\n\n```\nScoresStandingsFixtures\n```\n\nThese start with:\n\n```\nWhat is happening right now?\n```\n\nNotice the hierarchy:\n\n```\nStory↓Event↓Statistics\n```\n\nnot\n\n```\nStatistics↓Event↓Story\n```\n\nThe NBA screen leads with \"ADVANCE\".\n\nThe F1 screen leads with a dramatic race image.\n\nThe football screens lead with a single hero match.\n\nThey're selling narrative before information.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":4514,
			"y":-803,
			"width":460,
			"height":677
		},
		{
			"id":"c36a33ee855dce62",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Every Card Answers One Question\n\nGood discovery cards answer exactly one question.\n\nExamples:\n\n```\nWho is playing?\n```\n\nHero match card.\n\n```\nWhat is happening now?\n```\n\nLive rail.\n\n```\nWhat should I care about next?\n```\n\nUpcoming rail.\n\n```\nWhat happened recently?\n```\n\nLatest stories rail.\n\nNo card tries to do everything.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":5440,
			"y":-720,
			"width":360,
			"height":660
		},
		{
			"id":"1e439999fc32150c",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### ==Everything Is Designed Around FOMO==\n\nLook carefully.\n\nEvery screen contains temporal language:\n\n```\nHappening NowComing UpLatestLiveTomorrow\n```\n\nSports are valuable because they expire.\n\nThe UI constantly reminds users:\n\n```\nSomething important is happening right now.\n```\n\nThis creates urgency without notifications.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":5037,
			"y":-706,
			"width":360,
			"height":580
		},
		{
			"id":"08d021592849811d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":7500,
			"y":680,
			"width":260,
			"height":60
		},
		{"id":"b3854fb70e192e60","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260623022125.png","x":6860,"y":-159,"width":185,"height":400},
		{"id":"7edb261a2bb2d28e","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260623024448.png","x":7060,"y":-159,"width":185,"height":400},
		{"id":"a9434668d94de7aa","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123739.png","x":5234,"y":-40,"width":176,"height":400},
		{
			"id":"3a48156017e82236",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Notice How Few Words Exist\n\nExtremely important.\n\nThe less certainty a user has...\n\nThe less text designers use.\n\nTravel discovery is high uncertainty.\n\nUsers don't know:\n\n- where\n- when\n- what\n\nSo the interface leans heavily on visuals.\n\nCompare this to finance.\n\nFinance apps are mostly numbers.\n\nTravel apps are mostly imagery.\n\nThe UI mirrors the decision type.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1240,
			"y":-960,
			"width":440,
			"height":400
		},
		{
			"id":"c1864757b79b0933",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==The Real Hero Component Is The Horizontal Rail==\n\nNotice:\n\n- story cards\n- collections\n- categories\n- books\n\nEvery screen contains horizontal scrolling.\n\nWhy?\n\nBecause horizontal scrolling creates:\n\n### Low Commitment Discovery\n\nVertical scroll means:\n\n```\nLeave current thingMove elsewhere\n```\n\nHorizontal means:\n\n```\nPeekWithout leaving context\n```\n\nHuge psychological difference.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1731,
			"y":1301,
			"width":520,
			"height":720
		},
		{
			"id":"c6b15786160533e1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## 1. Hide Infinite Possibility Behind Small Choices\n## 2. Frontload Momentum, Not Discovery\n## 3. The White Space Is Doing More Work Than The Content\n## 4. The Designers Are Fighting \"Choice Paralysis\"\n## 5. The ==Hidden Metric They Probably Optimize For== Not: Views,  Not: Time on screen, ==Probably: Time-to-first-action==\n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3766,
			"y":1433,
			"width":660,
			"height":417
		},
		{
			"id":"40f7b360f9a53560",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Travel is hard to evaluate -One image=1000 words of evaluation\n\nA location has:\n\n- weather\n- culture\n- food\n- atmosphere\n- activities\n- vibe\n\nImpossible to explain quickly.\n\nA single image compresses all of it.\n\nThe designer is essentially saying:\n\n```\nOne image=1000 words of evaluation\n```\n\nThis is why the photos dominate the screen.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1700,
			"y":-960,
			"width":680,
			"height":400
		},
		{
			"id":"18a6db71e36b3792",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# HORIZONTAL  vs VERTICAL SCROLL PLAY",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2342,
			"y":1759,
			"width":280,
			"height":181
		},
		{
			"id":"cf12474b93f0c3f0",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### ==Trending + Newly Opened = exploration engine==\n\nThese labels create continuous novelty.\n\nWithout them:\n\n```\nRestaurant Database\n```\n\nWith them:\n\n```\nLiving City\n```\n\nThe screen feels alive because content appears time-sensitive",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3340,
			"y":1441,
			"width":360,
			"height":409
		},
		{
			"id":"19b3bb1be7bf13d5",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==They Separate \"Exploration\" And \"Commitment\"==\n\nNotice the funnel.\n\n### Lightweight\n\nStories\n\nCategories\n\nCollections\n\nTags\n\n↓\n\n### Medium\n\nChallenges\n\nBooks\n\nCourses\n\n↓\n\n### Heavy\n\nLong-form learning\n\nReading streaks\n\nPrograms",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2681,
			"y":1319,
			"width":378,
			"height":880
		},
		{"id":"864bcfa32a5a2d76","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124057.png","x":1240,"y":-479,"width":368,"height":400},
		{"id":"9d2d0435689b6aa0","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124237.png","x":2181,"y":-470,"width":521,"height":391},
		{
			"id":"7fb4e7fcb04d04cd",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ==The Feed Is Not Organized Around Content==\n\nThis is the deepest observation.\n\nA novice designer sees:\n\n```\ncontent sections\n```\n\nA senior designer sees:\n\n```\nbehavior sections\n```\n\nExample:\n\n### Continue\n\nResume existing behavior.\n\n### Explore\n\nFind new behavior.\n\n### Challenge\n\nCommit to behavior.\n\n### Collection\n\nOrganize behavior.\n\n### Recommended\n\nExpand behavior.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":693,
			"y":279,
			"width":560,
			"height":1029
		},
		{"id":"ea71173d91fb2e07","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622123912.png","x":880,"y":1420,"width":177,"height":400},
		{"id":"6cc27b59408d7bb5","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622125033.png","x":1072,"y":1433,"width":176,"height":399},
		{"id":"717bf7378efd4c30","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622125215.png","x":1272,"y":1433,"width":176,"height":399},
		{"id":"f860773db61c67f9","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622125222.png","x":1472,"y":1433,"width":176,"height":399},
		{
			"id":"55d13b16103ea5b1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### The Product Page Has Almost No Navigation\n\nLook carefully.\n\nVery few exits.\n\nVery few distractions.\n\nAlmost everything points toward:\n\n```\nAdd To Cart\n```\n\nThe designers know:\n\nEvery alternative path is a conversion leak.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":2442,
			"y":-993,
			"width":460,
			"height":400
		},
		{
			"id":"cc568a1d8d771fb3",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Large Hero Cards Reduce Comparison Fatigue\n\nVery interesting pattern.\n\nThe designers intentionally show:\n\nONE destination.\n\nBIG.\n\nNot:\n\n20 destinations simultaneously.\n\nWhy?\n\nBecause comparison kills momentum.\n\nWhen users see:\n\n```\nBaliSantoriniIcelandJapanMaldivesSwiss Alps\n```\n\nThe brain starts evaluating.\n\nEvaluation is expensive.\n\nThe hero card forces temporary commitment:\n\n```\nFocus on this.Imagine this.Feel this.\n```\n\nOnly later compare.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1320,
			"y":117,
			"width":366,
			"height":829
		},
		{"id":"3baf038bed3d386e","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124227.png","x":1640,"y":-479,"width":533,"height":400},
		{
			"id":"a56395475e87c04f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### The card is optimized for emotional decision-making\n\nLook at the information order:\n\n```\nPhoto↓\nName↓\nTags↓\nSocial proof↓\nAction\n```\n\nNot:\n\n```\nName\nRating\nDistance\nPrice\n```\n\nThis is inspiration-first.\n\nThe image sells.\n\nThe metadata just justifies.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":4554,
			"y":460,
			"width":520,
			"height":580
		},
		{"id":"947f2b6b44efaf2c","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124125.png","x":4600,"y":-40,"width":374,"height":400},
		{
			"id":"7d90952f30423721",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### The map is intentionally low-information\n\nThe map is blurred and simplified.\n\nYou can't really navigate from it.\n\nThat's because the map isn't serving navigation.\n\nIt's serving orientation.\n\nIts job is:\n\n```\nWhere am I exploring?\n```\n\nnot\n\n```\nHow do I get there?\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3606,
			"y":36,
			"width":440,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"2569711799e26bab",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### ==The card width is almost screen width==\n\nThis creates:\n\n```\nOne primary decision\n```\n\nrather than\n\n```\nMany competing decisions\n```\n\nPinterest maximizes options.\n\nThis screen maximizes commitment.\n\nThe user spends longer evaluating each candidate.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":3606,
			"y":630,
			"width":300,
			"height":473
		},
		{
			"id":"21042e8b842cdbe7",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"## Use Progressive Information Disclosure\n\nObserve destination details.\n\nInitially:\n\n```\nBeautiful imageSmall title\n```\n\nThen:\n\n```\nPreview\n```\n\nThen:\n\n```\nFull destination page\n```\n\nThen:\n\n```\nBook Now\n```\n\nInformation expands alongside commitment.\n\nThis prevents overwhelm.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":1869,
			"y":36,
			"width":382,
			"height":652
		},
		{"id":"0cae5b3efa6301fa","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124543.png","x":2352,"y":158,"width":180,"height":409},
		{"id":"d080b6d6286c4ff5","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124042.png","x":1774,"y":764,"width":516,"height":362},
		{"id":"c312af03adddeccf","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622125107.png","x":2328,"y":688,"width":227,"height":516},
		{
			"id":"dece9f27f3937099",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### ==Social proof is embedded, not explicit==\n\nNotice:\n\n```\n31 peoplesaved from Instagram\n```\n\ninstead of:\n\n```\n4.7 stars1,238 reviews\n```\n\nThat's deliberate.\n\nHumans trust:\n\n> \"People like me found this\"\n\nmore than\n\n> \"Algorithm score = 4.7\"",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":4160,
			"y":688,
			"width":320,
			"height":530
		},
		{"id":"ff0206799e92bd9d","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260622124604.png","x":3932,"y":667,"width":177,"height":400},
		{
			"id":"ff6cbf022b740ba2",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### Categories are lightweight filters\n\nThe chips aren't acting like navigation.\n\nThey're acting like lenses.\n\n```\nRestaurant\nCafe\nBar\nShop\n```\n\ndoesn't change screens.\n\nIt changes the flavor of discovery.\n\nVery important distinction.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":4080,
			"y":36,
			"width":360,
			"height":424
		},
		{"id":"963ac76c90e6d90d","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260623024600.png","x":6260,"y":-200,"width":260,"height":549},
		{"id":"149a98f0e3968c11","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260623022225.png","x":6520,"y":-200,"width":260,"height":549},
		{"id":"433b1615a9f1f75d","type":"file","file":"zManagment/Media/Pasted image 20260624184955.png","x":5440,"y":91,"width":400,"height":239}
	],
